review_blob: nice fresh hop aroma and taste at the first taste.  light head.  Like a good IPA without the heavy bitterness which is ummm like a good APA.   Nice drinkable beer.

Bottle.  Black.   Not just dark.  no light passes through.   Nice amber head.  hops aroma and taste envelope this brew in spite of the solid maltiness.   Very enjoyable.  Share it with a friend or you may be done after one.
beer_name: Stone 15th Anniversary Escondidian Imperial Black IPA

review_blob: Nice Black IPA.  Malt, as expected, hides the hops diminishing the overall IPA feel but this is not a regular IPA.   I enjoyed a couple over appetizers of all sorts and it held it own with them all.
great holiday ale.   Oats adds thickness.  spices meld wonderfully in aroma and taste.
beer_name: Ngne  / Jolly Pumpkin / Stone Special Holiday Ale

review_blob: Nice hoppy aroma.  crisp unmistaken pils finish.   My favorite pils.  I am an IPA hop hound and Prima provides the lightness of a Pils for quenching and enough hops to make one feel near their hoppy home.   Planning to home brew this soon if I can get the right lagering temp.

Reminded me of ABA my first taste but the malt is stronger in this brew.  Nice hop bitterness but not too aromatic in the fruitiness of some IPAs.   A good strong ale.   Not many out there to choose from.

Had it on tap a couple weeks ago in Boulder at West End Tavern.  At the time, it was described as a stone IPA with roasted dark malts.   It was so much more.   I love ABA and this was somewhere between ABA and their IPA.  Outstanding.    Sorry I cant be more deScriptive of all the flavors.
beer_name: Stone Sublimely Self Righteous Black IPA

review_blob: very nice IPA.   Drank copious amounts on a recent trip to the mountains.   Hop aroma is a nice anticipation for the taste.   My brother and I both noted that the citrus and pine hoppy flavor made the bitterness less intense.   Best of both worlds.

Hops are very evident in the aroma and taste.   I am an IPA guy and though this pilsner is lighter in it feel than an IPA, the strength of the brew is clear.    The german hops are different than what I am used to from some of the more famous hop ales out there.    not quite as fruity.   The Pilsner aspect almost gets lost in the hops but not quite.  Nice.

Had this on tap and in the bottle.   Nice hoppiness with some depth.  A piney hop aroma.  Not over hopped or over bitter.   Sweetness may allow some IPA haters a chance.    Not likely.   I know, its starting to sound like a Stone bottle.   All IPAs all assault the palate and this one is a good choice.

Light in color.   Not overly hoppy. Smooth flavor with a nice finish.   It feels lighter than most IPAs which makes it attractive for summer consumption.   Their brew schedule of July-september seems to fit.   I too have been waiting for this brew from Great Lakes.

This is a solid IPA that lacks a little depth but still holds on the good hoppiness of the type.   I could drink a few of these in a  summertime atmosphere.  Some IPAs are heavier and more for winter.
beer_name: Flying Fish HopFish India Pale Ale

review_blob: This was my First Altbier.  Hops present and good.  Malt hangs on the palate.     Satisfying in its depth of flavors.  Need this in Ohio.

Hoppiness.   Good.  Aroma very IPAish.   Drank from a bottle so no comment on color.  Flavor good but not too deep.   Hop bitter due to the reaction of friends who prefer to worship at the altar of ALB (American Light Beers).   All in all, this beer was a satsifying IPA.  Not the best I have had but solid.
Good Dark beer.  I am not an officianado of Porters but this beer was pleasant to drink.  I got a 12-pack variety pack of Arcadia.  This may be the best even though I am partial to IPAs.

I have had this beer on tap and from the bottle.  Nice dark color for an IPA.  It is hard to beat The_Beer_Gods deScription.  Pine, citrus, a little malt.   The bottled version seems to have more to it than on-tap.    All around pretty decent micro brew from my home town.
Smooth pale ale.  fruitier than Bass.  Not as hoopy as I like.  not bitter enough but maybe that is how English pale ales are.  I had a fresh bottle from the brewery.
beer_name: Church Brew Pipe Organ Pale Ale

review_blob: citrus flavor, nice amber color. will try again locally when I see my bro in boulder.
beer_name: Boulder Beer Hazed Hoppy Session Ale

review_blob: Great Brew.   Darkness is attractive.  Smooth.  Everyone who I see try this beer likes it.  Premium.

A nice smooth tastful lager.  I am never disappointed to see Honey Brown as a selection in the cooler.   My best experience was drinking it on-tap, at a local place in Cooks Forest PA, while eating whole spicey chicken wings.  A great mix.
The hoppiness is very smooth.  It starts bitter and smooths right out revealing a depth of flavor.  I never get sick of this ale.  Available at local bevy stores.
This beer is so impressive that it has a god named ABA in a Pantheon of Mantrip golf gods.  Lesser beer drinkers should go have a Bud Light with their tail between their legs.
